Hi twins14, I am new to TF myself. What I have been doing is going over the mnist tutorial, which is basically just classifying numbers in photos: https://www.tensorflow.org/get_started/mnist/beginners with the actual code you can run here: https://github.com/tensorflow/tensorflow/blob/master/tensorflow/examples/tutorials/mnist/mnist.py I have moved on to the graph visualizations tutorial here: https://www.tensorflow.org/get_started/summaries_and_tensorboard and code for it here: https://github.com/tensorflow/tensorflow/blob/r1.1/tensorflow/examples/tutorials/mnist/mnist_with_summaries.py I think understanding the visualization portion will be very important if you want to actually test your code. Goodluck!

body:
Hi twins14,

I am new to TF myself.  What I have been doing is going over the mnist
tutorial, which is basically just classifying numbers in photos:

https://www.tensorflow.org/get_started/mnist/beginners

with the actual code you can run here:

https://github.com/tensorflow/tensorflow/blob/master/tensorflow/examples/tutorials/mnist/mnist.py

I have moved on to the graph visualizations tutorial here:

https://www.tensorflow.org/get_started/summaries_and_tensorboard

and code for it here:

https://github.com/tensorflow/tensorflow/blob/r1.1/tensorflow/examples/tutorials/mnist/mnist_with_summaries.py

I think understanding the visualization portion will be very important if
you want to actually test your code.  Goodluck!
